summary: This is an email exchange between FBI personnel regarding a request for assistance for Squad C-20 (VCACIHT) related to the ongoing Epstein/Maxwell investigation. It highlights the high-profile nature of the case and the coordination of resources within the FBI's New York Field Office.

persons.name: Tracy
persons.context: Appears to be the sender of the initial request for assistance for Squad C-20 related to the Epstein/Maxwell investigation, and is copied on the response for visibility.

events.title: FBI Request for Assistance on Epstein/Maxwell Case
events.description: FBI Squad C-20 (VCACIHT) sends a request for assistance related to the ongoing Epstein/Maxwell investigation, describing it as a unique opportunity on a high-profile case.

keyFacts: The FBI's Squad C-20 (VCACIHT) was actively seeking assistance for the Epstein/Maxwell investigation as of July 29, 2020.
The case is described internally as a 'high profile case' and a 'unique opportunity' for agents.
The communication indicates ongoing investigative activity and resource coordination within the FBI's New York Field Office related to the case.
